proof: let [T0] (s1: (T0 -> Bool) -> lib(list.list_base).List[T0], s2: (T0 -> Bool, lib(list.list_base).List[T0]) -> T0) satisfy { forall(x0: T0 -> Bool, x1: T0) { not lib(set).finite_constraint[T0](x0) or not x0(x1) or x1 ∈ s1(x0) } and forall(x2: T0 -> Bool, x3: lib(list.list_base).List[T0]) { lib(set).finite_constraint[T0](x2) or x2(s2(x2, x3)) } and forall(x4: lib(list.list_base).List[T0], x5: T0 -> Bool) { not s2(x5, x4) ∈ x4 or lib(set).finite_constraint[T0](x5) } }
not Set.empty_set[T].is_empty or not s2(Set.empty_set[T].contains, s0) ∈ Set.empty_set[T]
